(602, 'manual', 'vbadvanced', '[ul] 	[li]On step 1, download the file ''ezstats2_bf3.php''.[/li] 	[li]Upload the file to the folder ''modules'' of your vBadvanced installation[/li] 	[li]Go tho the vBulletin Admin, then to the vb-cmps-secton[/li] 	[li]Click onto ''add new page'', select as the type of the pafe ''PHP File''[br](Pages will allow you to specify a file from anywhere on your server that will be displayed as the content for the page.)[/li] 	[li]Then go through each setting and enter the path to the plugin file: ''modules/ezstats2_bf3.php''[/li] 	[li]Then also enable these menu points: ''Clean File Output'', ''Use Module Wrapper Template'', ''Wrap a Table Around Content''[/li] 	[li]Enable the page and go view it :)[/li] [/ul]', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(603, 'manual', 'vbulletin41', '[ul] 	[li]On step 1, download the file ''ezStats2.php''.[/li] 	[li]Open the Adminpanel of vBulletin, go to ''vBulletin CMS -> Widgets'' and click onto ''Create New Widget''.[/li] 	[li]As ''Widget Type'' choose ''PHP Direct Execution'', and enter as title ''Leaderboard of Clanname'' for example. Click onto ''Save'' then.[/li] 	[li]In the list of widget, your new widget appears now. Click onto ''Configure'' and copy the content of the file ''ezStats2.php'' into the textfield there. Click onto ''Save'' then.[/li] 	[li]In the Adminpanel of vBulletin, go to ''vBulletin CMS -> Layouts'', and edit the layout, in which you want to add the leaderboard.[/li] 	[li]Select in the widgetlist your new widget, and drag it in your favourite position. Click onto ''Save'' then.[/[/li] 	[li]The leaderboard appears now in the layout you have edited![/li] [/ul]', '[ul] 	[li]Lade unter Schritt 1 die Datei ''ezStats2.php'' herunter.[/li] 	[li]Gehe in das Adminpanel von vBulletin und gehe zu ''vBulletin CMS -> Widgets'' und klicke auf ''Create New Widget''.[/li] 	[li]Als ''Widget Type'' wÃƒÂ¤hle ''PHP Direct Execution'' aus, und als Titel z.B. ''Leaderboard von Clanname''. Klicke auf ''Save''.[/li] 	[li]In der Widgetliste erscheint nun das neue Widget. Klicke nun auf ''Configure'' und kopiere in das Textfeld den Inhalt der Datei ''ezStats2.php'' hinein. Danach klicke auf ''Save''.[/li] 	[li]Gehe nun im Adminpanel auf ''vBulletin CMS -> Layouts'', such dir das Layout aus in dem das Leaderboard erscheinen soll, und editiere es.[/li] 	[li]Such dir in der Widgetliste das neue Widget aus, und positioniere es dort, wo du das Leaderboard haben willst. Klicke danach auf ''Save''.[/li] 	[li]Das Leaderboard wird nun in dem von dir bearbeiteten Layout angezeigt.[/li] [/ul]', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
